@stalary Do you make sure kafka-v1-plugin support V2?
I work a little on this, I found V1 is basically compatible with V2 without COMSUMER. Maybe we just  need to compate with COMSUER.
In another hand, DockerFile of testcase has some problem need to fix.

> Do you make sure kafka-v1-plugin support V2?

@dmsolr  Yes, I went through some local tests and the producers didn't find any problems.

Consumers changed from the original pollOnce to pollForFetches, so I need to modify getMethodsMatcher to make it compatibility, and I plan to enrich the information of tags and add MQ_QUEUE to represent the key in production and the groud.id in consumption, how do you feel?
